c: 39
v: 38
t: "And if you ask them: \"Who created the heavens and the Earth\", they will Say: \"God.\" Say: \"Do you see what you call on besides God, If God wanted any harm for me, can they alleviate His harm Or if He wanted a mercy for me, can they hold back his mercy\" Say: \"God is sufficient for me; in Him those who trust shall put their trust"